  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mainstreaming Human Rights into Immigration and Border Management</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims at identifying best practices in, and challenges to the protection of human rights at international borders, in order to properly integrate human rights principles in the training and practice of border control agents and ensure that migrants traversing or attempting to traverse those borders, enjoy the protection of their fundamental rights. The project also supports the rollout of a capacity-building / training package tailored at border management practitioners. Finally, the project aims at mainstreaming best practices identified during the project cycle into internal processes and guidelines.</narrative>
  </description>
